---

{# ── SUMMARY · real H2 carrying the short-version prose (right after the in-brief). (H2: The short version.) ── #}
<section class="section section--compact" id="ny-svc-speak-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">In short</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">The short version.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="stack-8">
      {%- for p in summary %}<p class="prose">{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── WHO + SPLIT · who should talk to a ProAdvisor vs. who Intuit should handle (grid-2 buyer-cards). Sheet-7 intent-split, ABOVE the funnel content. (H2: Is a ProAdvisor call the right call?) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-svc-speak-split">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Who should call &mdash; and who Intuit should handle</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Is a ProAdvisor call the right call?</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">A discovery call with this team is about <strong>your own books</strong> &mdash; how your QuickBooks file is set up and run. It is not Intuit support. The split below tells you where to go.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for s in split %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <p class="buyer-card__opener">{{ s.tag | safe }}</p>
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">{{ s.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
        <ul class="checks-list">{%- for li in s.list %}<li>{{ li | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}</ul>
        {%- if s.cta %}<a class="buyer-card__cta" href="{{ s.href }}"{% if s.rel %} rel="{{ s.rel }}"{% endif %}>{{ s.cta | safe }}</a>{%- endif %}
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="prose">{{ splitNote | safe }}</p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── AI SUMMARY · five-question block. (H2: Talking to a New York ProAdvisor, in five questions.) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-svc-speak-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Talking to a New York ProAdvisor, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <dl class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled" id="ny-svc-speak-ai-summary-list">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <dt class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</dt>
        <dd class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></dd>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </dl>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── CONVERSATION · how the call runs (grid-3 buyer-cards). 3 frozen H3s verbatim. (H2 + 3 H3s) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-svc-speak-conversation">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What to expect on the call</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">A real conversation, not a sales funnel.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">You speak with a Certified ProAdvisor &mdash; the kind of person who would do or oversee the work &mdash; not a salesperson and not a product-support queue. Here is how it goes.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for c in conversation %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <p class="buyer-card__opener">{{ c.num | safe }}</p>
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">{{ c.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ c.body | safe }}</p>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── COVERS vs NOT · what the call covers and what it is NOT (Intuit support) (grid-2 buyer-cards). Sheet-7 boundary restated explicitly. (H2: What the call covers — and what it does not.) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-svc-speak-covers">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The boundary, stated plainly</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What the call covers &mdash; and what it does not.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">So no one wastes a call: here is exactly what a ProAdvisor can help with, and what only Intuit can.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for c in covers %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <p class="buyer-card__opener">{{ c.tag | safe }}</p>
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">{{ c.title | safe }}</h3>
        <ul class="checks-list">{%- for li in c.list %}<li>{{ li | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}</ul>
        {%- if c.note %}<p class="buyer-card__body">{{ c.note | safe }}</p>{%- endif %}
        {%- if c.cta %}<a class="buyer-card__cta" href="{{ c.href }}"{% if c.rel %} rel="{{ c.rel }}"{% endif %}>{{ c.cta | safe }}</a>{%- endif %}
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── ADVISORY · standing brand line carried as section prose. (H2: Automation handles the data entry. We handle the judgment.) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-svc-speak-advisory">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The advisory line</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Automation handles the data entry. We handle the judgment.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="stack-8">
      {%- for p in advisoryBody %}<p class="prose">{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <div class="hero__actions">
      <a class="btn btn--primary btn--lg" href="/contact/?intent=new-york&amp;state=new-york&amp;source_type=state-money&amp;funnel_stage=BOFU">Book the discovery call</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── FAQ · 8 verbatim contract Q/A; visible faq__list = FAQPage schema (same array). (H2: Questions about speaking with a ProAdvisor.) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-svc-speak-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Common questions</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Questions about speaking with a ProAdvisor.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="ny-svc-speak-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="ny-svc-speak-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── EXPERT REVIEW · firm-level, no founder name (byline-block + meta-reviewed). (H2: Reviewed by the TechBrot Certified ProAdvisor team.) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-svc-speak-review">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Page review &amp; standards</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Reviewed by the TechBrot Certified ProAdvisor team.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="byline-block">
      <div class="byline-block__mark" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div>
        <p class="byline-block__name">By the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team</p>
        <p class="byline-block__review">TechBrot Inc. &middot; Independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Reviewed and maintained by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at <strong>TechBrot Inc.</strong>, a Delaware-incorporated independent ProAdvisor firm serving New York businesses across all 62 counties. Discovery calls are conducted by Certified ProAdvisors. TechBrot is an independent firm &mdash; not affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by <a href="https://www.intuit.com/" rel="noopener nofollow">Intuit Inc.</a>; it provides no Intuit account, billing, or QuickBooks product support. TechBrot performs bookkeeping and QuickBooks work and coordinates with your CPA, who files; it does not file New York tax returns or represent clients before the tax authorities.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for c in reviewCreds %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ c.label }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ c.detail | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="meta-reviewed"><span>Published: 2026-06-07</span><span>Updated: 2026-06-07</span><span>Reviewed: 2026-06-07 &middot; Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor</span></p>
  </div>
</section>
